### Friend List Structure and Ranking Logic

- Friend list is split into two tabs:
  - Tab 1: New Tap-Ins
    - Chronologically ordered by most recent first tap
    - Shows people you have connected with for the first time recently
    - Surfaces new relationships before they get buried
  - Tab 2: Top 10 (working name)
    - Ranked by frequency of tap-ins over time
    - The 10 people you have physically met and tapped with most often
    - Functions as a “closest friends” signal derived from behavior, not self-selection
    - Analogous to Snapchat’s Best Friends / streak mechanic, but grounded in physical meetings
- Recency vs. frequency as dual signals
  - New Tap-Ins = recency signal (who have I just met?)
  - Top 10 = frequency signal (who do I actually spend time with?)
  - Together they give a full picture of both new and established relationships

