### Business Profile Mechanics

- Businesses join as a distinct profile type
  - Physical NFC sticker or tappable device installed at the business location
  - The only way to follow a business is to physically visit and tap in
  - No remote follows, no “like our page” equivalent
- Implications for the business:
  - Follower list = verified visitor list
  - Every follower has been physically present at least once
  - Businesses can see:
    - Total unique visitors (tapped at least once)
    - Regulars: users who have tapped in multiple times
    - Frequency distribution: how often each follower visits
  - This data is structurally unavailable on any current social platform
- Content model for businesses:
  - Posts are only visible to people who have tapped in (i.e. verified visitors)
  - Encourages humanized, staff-led content rather than polished brand assets
    - Example: “Steve from La Carnita” posting day-in-the-life content vs. a restaurant’s generic promo photo
  - Businesses cannot reach non-visitors organically; content is inherently targeted
- Promotions and messaging use cases:
  - Tap-in discount: “20% off if you tap in today” — only visible to existing followers (verified visitors)
  - Secret menu or exclusive offer via DM: sent only to followers, e.g. “Tuesday happy hour secret menu, this month only”
  - Re-engagement promo: nudge lapsed visitors with a time-limited offer
  - All promotions are high-signal by design: recipient has already been to the venue
- Regulars tracking as CRM replacement:
  - Traditional social media: thousands of followers, no way to distinguish regulars from one-time visitors
  - This app: tap frequency per user = visit frequency data
  - Businesses can identify their top 10% most loyal customers without any additional tooling
  - Future feature: loyalty tier system based on tap count (e.g. bronze/silver/gold regular)

