### Next Steps and Open Questions

- Immediate priorities:
  - Enable and fully test chat functionality (identified as a core, non-negotiable feature)
  - Test NFC tap connection flow across a range of Android and iOS devices
  - Gather early user feedback on core loop: tap → friend → post → reconnect
- Design decisions to resolve:
  - Unfriend notification wording: A/B test anonymous vs. named variants
  - Friend list tab naming: “New Tap-Ins” and “Top 10” are working names
  - Location nudge opt-in UX: how to present the city-level sharing prompt without alarming users
- Open product questions:
  - Should there be an optional friendship expiry/inactivity threshold?
  - How to handle users who meet abroad and will never realistically re-tap (valid friendship vs. dead weight)?
  - At what friend count does the anonymous unfriend notification become effectively meaningless?
  - Should the Top 10 be visible to others or only to the user themselves?
- Later-phase work:
  - Spotify integration design and OAuth flow
  - Business profile onboarding and NFC sticker provisioning
  - White-label partnership framework (Activate and similar venues)
  - Monetization model selection and pricing research
